Source: pdi
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Julien Bigot <julien.bigot@cea.fr>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), ifdef(`WITH_FORTRAN_MOD', `
  dh-fortran-mod,')ifdef(`WITH_TESTING',`
  cmake (>= 3.10),
  libgtest-dev (>= 1.8.0),
  libgmock-dev (>= 1.8.0),',`
  cmake (>= 3.5),')
  gfortran | fortran-compiler,
  bpp,
  pkg-config,
  libparaconf-dev (>= 0.4.0),
  libspdlog-dev (>= 1:1.3.1)
Standards-Version: 4.5.0
Homepage: https://pdi.julien-bigot.fr/

Package: libpdi0
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: pdiplugin-trace, pdiplugin-user-code
Suggests: pdiplugin-decl-hdf5, pdiplugin-mpi
Description: the Portable Data Interface library
 PDI is a library that aims to decouple high-performance simulation
 codes from Input/Output concerns.

Package: libpdi-f90.0
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libpdi0 (= ${binary:Version})
Description: the Portable Data Interface library
 PDI is a library that aims to decouple high-performance simulation
 codes from Input/Output concerns.

Package: libpdi-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libpdi-f90.0 (= ${binary:Version}), libparaconf-dev (>= 0.4.0), libspdlog-dev (>= 1.3.1)
Recommends: cmake (>= 3.5), pkg-config
Description: Development files for pdi
 The pdi-dev package contains C/C++/Fortran header files for developing
 applications or plugins that use pdi.
